The paper deals with abstraction in probabilistic models, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of first-order logic and stochastic primitives suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on modeling and reasoning about systems suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and security (cs.CR). Finally, the mention of hierarchical constructs suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
